11 An Act relating to stalking; amending Section 3,
Chapter 318, O.S.L. 2022 (21 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
12 1173.1), which relates to procedures for serving
Stalking Warning Letters; directing law enforcement
13 agencies to provide certain notification to victims
of stalking; deleting procedures for serving Stalking
14 Warning Letters; deleting service requirements and
Stalking Warning Letter form; removing requirement to
15 enter Stalking Warning Letters onto national
database; deleting document filing requirement; and
16 providing an effective date.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 3, Chapter 318, O.S.L.
21 2022 (21 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section 1173.1), is amended to read as
22 follows:
23 Section 1173.1. A. Whenever a law enforcement agency receives
24 a complaint of stalking and finds that such conduct has occurred,
HB1002 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 the law enforcement agency shall be required to provide a copy of a
2 Stalking Warning Letter to the accused provided that the victim does
3 not otherwise request that such letter not be served upon the
4 accused. The Stalking Warning Letter shall be served upon the
5 accused in the same manner as a bench warrant. If the service is to
6 be in another county, the court clerk may issue service to the
7 sheriff by facsimile or other electronic transmission for service by
8 the sheriff and may receive the return of service from the sheriff
9 in the same manner
10 B. The following statutory form of the Stalking Warning Letter,
11 as required by the provisions of subsection A of this section, shall
12 be utilized by law enforcement agencies throughout the state:
13 __________________________________ COUNTY, STATE OF OKLAHOMA
14 CITY OF _______________________________
15 RE: _______________________________________________________________
16 (COMPLAINANT)
17 Stalking Warning Letter served to: _________________________________
18 _________________________________
19 (HOME ADDRESS)
20 _________________________________
21 (DATE OF BIRTH)
22 The __________________________ has recently investigated a complaint
23 (LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY)
24 about your behavior towards the above-named individual.
HB1002 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 The behavior you have engaged in could be interpreted as "stalking"
2 as provided for in Section 1173 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
3 Statutes. Stalking can be described as intentionally engaging in a
4 course of conduct directed at a specific person that would cause a
5 reasonable person under the same circumstances to suffer serious
6 emotional distress, or place the specific person in reasonable fear
7 of bodily injury. Your behavior has induced such fear or distress
8 in the above-named individual.
9 Oklahoma law makes stalking a crime. The __________________________
10 (LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY)
11 takes this law very seriously.
12 Please consider this a formal warning that any future conduct by you
13 towards the above-named individual could result in arrest by law
14 enforcement and prosecution by the ______________________ County
15 District Attorney's Office.
16 _______________________________________________
17 Print name of Chief of Law Enforcement Agency
18 _______________________________________________
19 Signature of Chief of Law Enforcement Agency or designee
20 Served in hand __________________ by _______________________________
21 (DATE) (NAME OF OFFICER)
22 On behalf of the ____________________________________
23 (LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY)
24 at __________________________________________________
HB1002 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 (LOCATION) notify the victim of the availability
2 to meet with a representative of a certified domestic violence
3 program, as provided for in Section 18p-1 of Title 74 of the
4 Oklahoma Statutes.
5 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
6
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON JUDICIARY AND PUBLIC SAFETY
OVERSIGHT, dated 03/10/2025 - DO PASS, As Amended.
